SIMPLE: hospitalize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hospitalize
<hw>Hos"pi*tal*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>To render (a building) unfit for habitation, by
long continued use as a hospital.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To place (a person) in a hospital in order to
receive medical treatment, observation, or for rest.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hospitalise.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hospitate</ent>⟦br⟧
